NOTICE
======

Provenance
----------
This project interoperates with MATLAB(R) MEX files by way of an independent,
clean-room implementation of the publicly documented MATLAB C Matrix API (the
`mx*` and `mex*` functions and the `mxArray` type), derived solely from
MathWorks' public API documentation. It contains:

  * NO MathWorks header files (e.g. mex.h, matrix.h),
  * NO MathWorks source code, and
  * NO MathWorks binaries or libraries.

All function prototypes are declared independently. The purpose is
interoperability, not the reproduction of MATLAB or any of its components.

Unmex.jl bundles `runtime/libmxhost.c`, a from-scratch host implementation of
the `libmx`/`libmex` symbols a MEX file resolves at load time, so MEX files can
be loaded and called from Julia without a MATLAB installation. It calls back
into MATLAB only for behavior that lives in the MATLAB interpreter; such calls
raise a clear error rather than attempting to emulate the interpreter.

